div.p:
The six main areas of activity in HATII are:

it runs an academic programme in humanities computing at introductory,
                            honours, and postgraduate level;

it has responsibility for overseeing the development and management of
                            the departmentally based teaching laboratories and computer classrooms
                            for the Faculties of Divinity and Arts;

it supports and assists in the development and use of computing in
                            teaching within the two Faculties;

its technical team supplies a range of network services and desktop
                            support to Faculties of Divinity and Arts staff (~300), postgraduates
                            (~500), and undergraduates (~5000);

it acts to promote collaborative research projects within the two
                            Faculties; it manages a research programme;

it is organising and developing a range of conferences, summer
                            schools, and short courses.
